HEADWORD: Cavo-rilievo
<hw>Ca"vo-ri*lie"vo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[It.]</ety> <fld>(Sculp.)</fld> <def>Hollow relief; sculpture in
relief within a sinking made for the purpose, so no part of it projects
beyond the plain surface around.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

